MAPPING.DESCRIPTION:
This mapping sets start and end dates to next runs for all products. Values to product and period type should be set as variables.
This mapping sets five variables for a product-period pair:
$$m_RPTG_PERIOD_ID - Next rptg_period_id to be loaded (last r_bi_product_by_period.rptg_period_id that was published (bi_publish_flag = ?Y? for the product and for the period plus 1.)
$$m_RPTG_PERIOD_ST_DT - Period start date for next rptg_period_id $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_END_DT - Period end date for next rptg_period_id $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_ST_DT_ID - Calendar ID for period_start_date $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_END_DT_ID ? Calendar ID for period end date
Variables for reporting period type (WEEK, MONTH, QUARTER) and product name need to be set to use this mapping($$m_BI_PRODUCT_NAME and $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_TYPE respectively).
$$m_BI_PRODUCT_NAME should have values from d_bi_product.bi_product_name and $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_TYPE should have values from d_rptg_period_type. rptg_period_type_name.
For example:
$$m_BI_PRODUCT_NAME=ADPACK_SCORECARD $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_TYPE=MONTH
MAPPING.NAME: m_Product_Metrics_Set_Dates

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT drp.rptg_period_st_dt AS rptg_period_st_dt, drp.rptg_period_end_dt as rptg_period_end_dt, drp.rptg_period_st_dt_id as rptg_period_st_dt_id, drp.rptg_period_end_dt_id as rptg_period_end_dt_id, drp.rptg_period_id FROM d_rptg_period drp WHERE drp.rptg_period_id = ( SELECT bpp.rptg_period_id +1 as next_rptg_period_id FROM r_bi_product_by_period bpp INNER JOIN d_rptg_period drp ON bpp.rptg_period_id = drp.rptg_period_id INNER JOIN d_rptg_period_type drpt ON drp.rptg_period_type_id = drpt.rptg_period_type_id WHERE bi_product_id = (SELECT bi_product_id FROM d_bi_product WHERE bi_product_name = '$$m_BI_PRODUCT_NAME') AND bi_publish_flag_id = (SELECT bi_publish_flag_id FROM d_bi_publish_flag WHERE bi_publish_flag_code = 'Y') AND UPPER(drpt.rptg_period_type_name) = '$$m_RPTG_PERIOD_TYPE' )

NBR_OF_SHARED_EMAILS,NBR_OF_SHARED_PHONES AVG_NBR_OF_SAVED_CARS_MSA AVG_NBR_OF_SHARED_EMAILS_MSA AVG_NBR_OF_SHARED_PHONES_MSA AVG_NBR_OF_SAVED_CARS_NATL AVG_NBR_OF_SHARED_EMAILS_NATL AVG_NBR_OF_SHARED_PHONES_NATL

TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT COUNT( CASE WHEN UPPER( D.UCL_ACTION_TYPE) = 'VDPVIEWS' AND UPPER(V.HAS_ACCIDENTS) = 'N' THEN F.VIN END) AS UCL_TOTAL_NBR_NO_ACCIDENTS , COUNT( CASE WHEN UPPER( D.UCL_ACTION_TYPE) = 'VDPVIEWS' AND UPPER(V.SERVICE_RECORD_ICON) = 'WELLMAINTAINED' THEN F.VIN END) AS UCL_TOTAL_NBR_WELL_MAINTAINED , COUNT( CASE WHEN UPPER( D.UCL_ACTION_TYPE) = 'VDPVIEWS' AND UPPER(V.HAS_SERVICE_RECORDS) = 'Y' THEN F.VIN END) AS UCL_TOTAL_NBR_SERVICE_RECORDS , COUNT( CASE WHEN UPPER( D.UCL_ACTION_TYPE) = 'VDPVIEWS' AND UPPER(V.HAS_PERSONAL_USE) = 'Y' THEN F.VIN END) AS UCL_TOTAL_NBR_PERSONAL_USE , COUNT( CASE WHEN UPPER( D.UCL_ACTION_TYPE) = 'VDPVIEWS' AND UPPER(V.IS_ONE_OWNER) = 'Y' THEN F.VIN END) AS UCL_TOTAL_NBR_ONE_OWNER , R.PARENT_LOCATION_ID AS LOCATION_ID FROM F_UCL_ACTIONS F , D_UCL_ACTIONS D , R_ORG_RELATIONSHIP_BY_PERIOD R , D_VIN V WHERE F.UCL_ACTIONS_ID = D.UCL_ACTIONS_ID AND F.LOCATION_ID = R.CHILD_LOCATION_ID AND R.RPTG_PERIOD_ID = $$M_RPTG_PERIOD_ID AND F.VIN_ID = V.VIN_ID AND CAST(TO_CHAR(F.TRANSACTION_DATE, 'MM/DD/YYYY HH24:MI:SS') AS TIMESTAMP) >= V.EFFECTIVE_START_DT AND CAST(TO_CHAR(F.TRANSACTION_DATE, 'MM/DD/YYYY HH24:MI:SS') AS TIMESTAMP) <= NVL(V.EFFECTIVE_END_DT,SYSDATE) AND F.TRANSACTION_DATE_ID BETWEEN $$M_RPTG_PERIOD_ST_DT_ID AND $$M_RPTG_PERIOD_END_DT_ID AND F.UCL_VIN_EXPERIENCE_ID = ( SELECT DISTINCT UCL_VIN_EXPERIENCE_ID FROM D_UCL_VIN_EXPERIENCE WHERE UCL_VIN_EXPERIENCE_CODE = 'EE' ) GROUP BY R.PARENT_LOCATION_ID ORDER BY R.PARENT_LOCATION_ID --

TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT parent_location_id as location_id, SUM(record_type1_impression) as record_type1_impressions, SUM(record_type1_clicks) as record_type1_clicks, SUM(record_type2_impression) as record_type2_impressions, SUM(record_type2_clicks) as record_type2_clicks, SUM(record_type3_impression) as record_type3_impressions, SUM(record_type3_clicks) as record_type3_clicks from ( select parent_location_id, impression_record_type_id, is_impression, CASE WHEN is_impression ='I' and impression_record_type_id =1 THEN SUM(record_count) ELSE 0 END record_type1_impression, CASE WHEN is_impression ='C' and impression_record_type_id =1 THEN SUM(record_count) ELSE 0 END record_type1_clicks, CASE WHEN is_impression ='I' and impression_record_type_id =2 THEN SUM(record_count) ELSE 0 END record_type2_impression, CASE WHEN is_impression ='C' and impression_record_type_id =2 THEN SUM(record_count) ELSE 0 END record_type2_clicks, CASE WHEN is_impression ='I' and impression_record_type_id =3 THEN SUM(record_count) ELSE 0 END record_type3_impression, CASE WHEN is_impression ='C' and impression_record_type_id =3 THEN SUM(record_count) ELSE 0 END record_type3_clicks FROM f_impressions_clicks fic INNER JOIN r_org_relationship_by_period ror ON fic.location_id = ror.child_location_id INNER JOIN a_organization_metrics aom ON fic.location_id = aom.location_id WHERE aom.has_ucl_scorecard = 'Y' AND aom.rptg_period_id= $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_ID AND fic.record_date_id BETWEEN $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_ST_DT_ID AND $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_END_DT_ID AND ror.rptg_period_id = $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_ID GROUP BY parent_location_id,impression_record_type_id,is_impression ) GROUP BY location_id ORDER BY location_id --

SHORTCUT.COMMENTS:
This mapping sets start and end dates to next runs for all products. Values to product and period type should be set as variables.
This mapping sets five variables for a product-period pair:
$$m_RPTG_PERIOD_ID - Next rptg_period_id to be loaded (last r_bi_product_by_period.rptg_period_id that was published (bi_publish_flag = ?Y? for the product and for the period plus 1.)
$$m_RPTG_PERIOD_ST_DT - Period start date for next rptg_period_id $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_END_DT - Period end date for next rptg_period_id $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_ST_DT_ID - Calendar ID for period_start_date $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_END_DT_ID ? Calendar ID for period end date
Variables for reporting period type (WEEK, MONTH, QUARTER) and product name need to be set to use this mapping($$m_BI_PRODUCT_NAME and $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_TYPE respectively).
$$m_BI_PRODUCT_NAME should have values from d_bi_product.bi_product_name and $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_TYPE should have values from d_rptg_period_type. rptg_period_type_name.
For example:
$$m_BI_PRODUCT_NAME=ADPACK_SCORECARD $$m_RPTG_PERIOD_TYPE=MONTH
SHORTCUT.NAME: m_Product_Metrics_Set_Dates
